{
  "doc_id": "24570",
  "text": "Note also that these examples accomodate quantile estimation of ARCH-type processes, often used in modelling the conditional second moments of returns on financial assets; see [CITATION_1] for a treatment of quantile estimation in the finite-order ARCH model. Quantiles of both first and second moments of returns can be important in financial risk management. A form such as that in (4.1), with strictly positive values, would be appropriate for a quantity such as squared asset returns which are often treated with models from the ARCH class; the form in (4.2) would suit raw (possibly centred) asset returns, so that a lower-tail conditional quantile would correspond with the 'value at risk' (VaR).",
